    pageItem P60_TRADITIONAL_SANDBOX_REQS (
        type: displayOnly
        label {
            alignment: left
        }
        layout {
            sequence: 10
            region: @sandbox-forrm
            slot: regionBody
            alignment: left
        }
        appearance {
            template: @optional-floating
            templateOptions: #DEFAULT#
        }
        source {
            type: staticValue
            staticValue:
                ```
                Sandbox Requirements
                
                1.1 Does your sandbox require access to Cloud Shell?
                Yes or No
                
                1.2 Does your sandbox require a VCN? (LiveLabs can provision a VCN as part of the reservation setup with the standard Security List)
                Yes or No
                
                1.3 If yes, list the ports that must be opened for the workshop to function:
                Example: 129.146.0.0/21 port 22
                
                Resource Requirements
                
                2.1 List all resources that need to be provisioned by LiveLabs for your workshop
                (Do not list any resources that the user will spin up)
                Example: OKE Cluster - 1 Node
                
                2.2 List all resources that the user will provision while running the workshop
                (Do not list any resources provisioned by LiveLabs)
                Example: ADW - 1 ECPU
                Example: ADW - 1 TB
                
                Terraform
                
                3.1 Does your sandbox require a Terraform script?
                
                3.2 If yes, attend LiveLabs Office Hours to determine how best to proceed with creating your sandbox.
                
                Policies
                
                4.1 List all policies that users will need to complete your workshop
                (This should include access to both LiveLabs-provisioned resources and any resources users will create, edit, or delete)
                
                Example: Allow user to manage autonomous-database-family
                
                Image and Marketplace Questions
                
                5.1 Does your sandbox require the use of an image from OCI Marketplace?
                Yes or No
                
                5.2 Does your required image already exist and is used by another LiveLabs Sandbox?
                
                5.3 If yes, provide the following:
                WMS ID:
                LiveLabs ID:
                
                5.4 If no, you will need to create a Marketplace Image and Listing for your sandbox. Attend LiveLabs Office Hours for assistance.
                
                5.5 After creating your image, provide the following:
                Marketplace App Listing OCID:
                Marketplace Image OCID:
                Marketplace Listing Resource Version:
                
                Additional Information
                
                6.1 Provide any additional information relevant to your sandbox that has not been included above
                
                Notes from LiveLabs Admin
                
                --For Official Use Only--
                ```
            used: always
        }
        serverSideCondition {
            type: item=value
            item: P60_TYPE
            value: Traditional
        }
    )

    pageItem P60_TYPE (
        type: radioGroup
        label {
            label: Sandbox Type
            alignment: left
        }
        settings {
            noOfCols: 3
            pageActionOnSelection: redirectSetValue
        }
        lov {
            type: staticValues
            staticValues: "STATIC2:Traditional;Traditional,Lite;Lite,LiveStack;LiveStack "
            displayExtraValues: false
            displayNullValue: false
        }
        layout {
            sequence: 30
            region: @general-information
            slot: regionBody
            alignment: left
        }
        appearance {
            template: @optional-above
            templateOptions: [
                #DEFAULT#
                margin-top-md
            ]
        }
        validation {
            valueRequired: true
        }
        source {
            formRegion: @request-a-sandbox
            column: TYPE
            dataType: varchar2
        }
        default {
            type: item
            item: P60_TYPE
        }
        help {
            helpText:
                ```html
                <b> Traditional (ECT: 1-2 weeks). </b> A Traditional Sandbox is an environment custom made by our LiveLabs Platform team. This option is best for LiveLabs with complex setup requirements. </br></br>
                <b> Lite (ECT: 1 business day). </b> A Sandbox Lite is the automated, simplified version of a Traditional Sandbox. This sandbox type allows you to choose what resources you want the </u>user to provision.</u> It is not suitable for automatic provisioning of resources (e.g. databases) or executables (e.g. terraform stacks, scripts, etc.). This is most suitable for LiveLabs with simple setup requirements. </br></br>
                <b> LiveStack (ECT: 1 business day). </b> A LiveStack Sandbox environment is meant for demo-based content. Simply upload your customized stack and select your base image. <a href="">Full Instructions</a>
                ```
        }
    )

